
INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR APOPCALEAPS
=========================================


Just run ./install to install APOPCALEAPS. This will first compile FLTK 1.1.10,
then it generates the user interface source code and compiles it.




The following software is assumed to be installed:

  * GNU LilyPond 2.12.1
        a music sheet typesetting program with export to MIDI
        (apt-get install lilypond)

  * TiMidity++
        a good MIDI player
        (apt-get install timidity timidity-patches)
        (if you want to use a different MIDI player, change programs.conf)

  * GV
        a viewer for PostScript files
        (apt-get install gv)
        (if you want to use a different viewer, change programs.conf)
